<chapter condition="TITLE=System Features: Beneficiary Advice Designer"
         role="TOPIC">
  <title>Beneficiary Advice Designer</title>

  <section condition="TITLE=System Features: Beneficiary Advice Designer"
           id="BAD" role="TOPIC">
    <title>Overview</title>

    <para role="TEXT">A bank administrator can define standard beneficiary
    advices, such as Invoice forms, for use by customers, to assist in
    streamlining of processing of documents between the bank, customers and
    beneficiaries.</para>

    <para role="TEXT">Selecting the Beneficiary Advice Designer displays a
    list of previously designed templates, and allows new templates to be
    defined.</para>
</section>
    <section>
      <title>Beneficiary Advice Designer - Navigation</title>

      <para>To navigate to the <emphasis role="bold">Beneficiary Advice
      Designer</emphasis> function, from the toolbar, select <emphasis>System
      Features</emphasis> from the home page, then select
      <emphasis>Beneficiary Advice Designer</emphasis> from the left
      navigation menu.</para>
    </section>

    <section role="ITEM">
      <title>Beneficiary Advice Designer - List</title>

      <para role="TEXT">When the Beneficiary Advice Designer is selected a
      list of all the existing templates previously defined , will be
      presented. You can search the list by entering search criteria in the
      <guilabel moreinfo="none">Template ID</guilabel> field at the top of the
      page.</para>

      <para role="TEXT">The list of existing customer templates has the
      following columns:<informaltable role="TEXT">
          <tgroup cols="2">
            <colspec colname="c1" colwidth="2.0*"/>

            <colspec colname="c2" colwidth="8.0*"/>

            <thead>
              <row>
                <entry valign="top"><para>Field</para></entry>

                <entry valign="top"><para>Description</para></entry>
              </row>
            </thead>

            <tbody>
              <row>
                <entry valign="top"><para> <guilabel moreinfo="none">Template
                ID</guilabel> </para></entry>

                <entry valign="top"><para>Name of the Beneficiary Advice
                template </para></entry>
              </row>

              <row>
                <entry valign="top"><para> <guilabel
                moreinfo="none">Description</guilabel> </para></entry>

                <entry valign="top"><para>Description of the
                template</para></entry>
              </row>

              <row>
                <entry valign="top"><para> <guilabel
                moreinfo="none">Associated Customers</guilabel>
                </para></entry>

                <entry valign="top"><para>Customer the template is available
                to. (All for all customers)</para></entry>
              </row>
            </tbody>
          </tgroup>
        </informaltable></para>

      <para role="TEXT">You can modify a Template by clicking the <guiicon
      moreinfo="none">Edit</guiicon> <inlinemediaobject>
          <imageobject>
            <imagedata fileref="../images/icon_edit.gif" role="ICON_EDIT"
                       width="4mm"/>
          </imageobject>
        </inlinemediaobject> icon in the right-hand column or delete it by
      clicking the <guibutton moreinfo="none">Delete</guibutton>
      <inlinemediaobject>
          <imageobject>
            <imagedata fileref="../images/icon_trash.gif" role="ICON_TRASH"
                       width="4mm"/>
          </imageobject>
        </inlinemediaobject> icon.</para>

      <para role="TEXT">Click the <guibutton moreinfo="none">Add a new
      Beneficiary Advice</guibutton> button at the bottom of the list to add a
      template.</para>

      <para role="TEXT"><guiicon moreinfo="none">Edit</guiicon> and <guibutton
      moreinfo="none">Add</guibutton> display the same form, but in the case
      of <guibutton moreinfo="none">Edit</guibutton> it is preset with the
      existing details of the template. After entering the details, click
      <emphasis role="bold">Save</emphasis> at the bottom of the form.</para>

